Hi ,
I am trying to configure Jira calender , I am able to view it but when i login through some other user i am not able to view the calender.
I get the following error:
{noformat}
Unable to load events of Design Date (d2e3be70-8a5c-4bcb-a8ac-156ea7d1e4fa): Unable to read response from http://localhost/rest/ical/1.0/ical/search/jql/events.ics?_=1346762587228&jql=project+%3D+%22ADS%22&dateFieldName=customfield_10902&includeFixVersions=false as iCalendar text. You may want to check the connection to MyJira 
{noformat}

Also i am not able to add a team calender on a confluence page . When i try to add one using team calender macro i get a the same pop up when we a a calender and after i add a calender the calender does not get added and i am not able to do anything on the page.

Please can someone help me ?

